<h2>Comparison of Terminology</h2>

<p>Different languages and communities use different terminology for similar 
things.  The translation table below is provided so that you can ensure you're 
on the same page as this site.  This site will use the Raku TOP terminology, 
which is similar to the SQL terminology.</p>

<table>
	<tr>
		<th>Raku TOP</th>
		<th>SQL</th>
		<th>xHarbour/xBase</th>
		<th>Spreadsheet</th>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>Table</td>
		<td>Table</td>
		<td>Database</td>
		<td>Sheet</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>View</td>
		<td>View</td>
		<td>?Workspace, ordBag</td>
		<td>to a certain extent, filters on sheets</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>Cursor</td>
		<td>Cursor</td>
		<td>?Workspace</td>
		<td></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>Column</td>
		<td>Column</td>
		<td>Field</td>
		<td>Column</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>Driver</td>
		<td></td>
		<td>RDD</td>
		<td>-</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>Schema (hierarchical if desired)</td>
		<td>Schema (MySQL doesn't do these, PostgreSQL does)</td>
		<td>Filesystem Directory (hierarchical)</td>
		<td>-</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td>Database</td>
		<td>Database</td>
		<td>Filesystem Directory (hierarchical)</td>
		<td>File</td>
	</tr>
</table>

</content>
